    {
      "type": "note_added",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-15T03:35:22Z",
      "actor": "Priya Narayanan",
      "details": "The rule uses sanctioned-list-v7 with include_cloud_provider_ips=true and classification_mode=strict. Dry-run showed 0 false positives but I suspect the issue is that cloud provider IPs in non-sanctioned regions are being classified against their physical region mapping. The rule config resolves cloud IPs to physical data center locations, but many legitimate customers run inference from cloud VMs in eu-west, ap-southeast, etc."
    },
    {
      "type": "note_added",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-15T03:38:47Z",
      "actor": "Elena Vasquez",
      "details": "Confirmed: the dry-run validation missed this because the sanctioned-list-v7 feed was updated on April 13 to include broader cloud provider IP ranges. The dry-run observation period started April 11 with the old feed. The feed update happened mid-observation but the dry-run stats were not reset."
    },
    {
      "type": "external_escalation",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-15T03:40:01Z",
      "actor": "Marcus Adeyemi",
      "details": "Initiating cross-org escalation to Stratos Networks for edge rule remediation. Meridian does not have direct access to modify edge rules in production."
    }
  ],
